<body>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Three High-EV Lessons</h1>
        </header>
        <main>
            <article>
                <ol>
                    <li>1. Take advanrage of face up range chop pot spots</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>Don't</b> chop when they have <b>too many folds</b></li>
                        <li>Look for nodes where a particular opponent <b>doesn't slowplay enough OOP</b></li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Always take your fold equity <b>when you have a huge draw</b> and your opponent has a lot of
                        potential folds<ul>
                            <li><b>Plan A:</b> Think \"How can i <b>win without showdown?</b>\"</li>
                            <li><b>Plan B:</b> The draw coming in</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Don't be afraid to make heavy exploitative adjustments<ul>
                            <li><b>Pay attention</b> to showdowns; note <b>strong deviations</b> or tendencies</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </article>
        </main>
    </div>

</body>

